    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1868-06-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1868-06-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="253" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d253">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                de Stoeckl</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1868-06-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 24, 1868.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Will Mr. de Stoeckl have the goodness to recall the attention of the
                            imperial government to the request which the United States government
                            has made for explanations concerning the alleged proceedings or
                            regulations affecting the freedom of the fisheries in the Sea of
                            Okhotsk? The subject is not unlikely to produce present uneasiness,
                            which would soon be inconvenient, and ultimately become a source of
                            regret.</p>
                <p>I avail myself of this occasion to offer to you the renewed assurance of
                            my very high consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Edward de Stoeckl</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c</hi>., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
